name: Cat treat dispenser
description:
This is an Archimedes screw-like mechanism that can dispense cat treats, among other things.
Here is the [onshape link](https://cad.onshape.com/documents/0c03c5c5149025bc83e8267d/w/14a9466621494e3156ec90d7/e/c708a279b39a02c037e91f48 "Cat treat dispenser | Onshape")

###Assembly

put the screw inside the chassis, putting the round hole in the screw to the peg in the chassis. **There are holes on both sides of the screw, but one has a flat part and the other is a circle. Make sure you are using the right hole!**
Then put the base on the chassis with the holes on the bottom of the chassis.
finally, put the top on the chassis by matching the shorter pegs to the cutouts in the chassis.

###Operation

You can either use a NEMA-17 size stepper motor or the included hand crank.
Either way, you should be able to connect it to the top of the screw.

I plan on using an adafruit nRF52832 and stepper motor wing to dispense a cat treat over Bluetooth. I will leave a link to that code here once it is done.

name: Dog collar tracker backplate
description:
Problem: You have a Tractive GPS LTE dog tracker and your very long necked sighthound wears a 2" wide martingale. Since these trackers are designed to mount on collars that are 1" or less wide, you have no way to attach the tracker to the collar.

Solution: This is a very simple adapter that you sew onto your dog's wide martingale collar, allowing you to attach your Tractive tracker parallel to the collar in the way it was originally intended. Because the collar is flexible, you should still be able to push the tracker's straps between the adapter and the collar when replacing the tracker after charging.

This will almost certainly also work on a 1 1/2" wide collar, but I haven't tested it.

Print with the ridged side up, of course. I printed these in PLA, but if your dog's outside a lot you may want to do it in ABS instead given PLA's dislike of UV.  Use lots of ironing.

name: MiniBow/BettaBow 2.5 40mm Evaporative Cooler
description:
As we move into warmer temperatures and higher humidity's, I have found my MiniBow/BettaBow 2.5 gallon tank creeping up into dangerous temperatures...


First, I had a rPi fan hat jerry-rigged over top of the feeding hole and found this worked well. So, I decided to design something a little more permanent.

I use a 40mm Noctua 5v PWM fan and 4 M3 bolts/nuts. You can use whichever fan you like. Make sure that the bolts aren't too long.

I have been using this now for a while and believe it makes enough of a difference to publish.

Tip: print with the fan mount flat against the bed.

name: échelle
description:
Designed up this dealer button to use in home games or have just as something laying around for any poker fan.  It was inspired by a dealer button in Pokerstars VR.

Printing:

Ring - Infil to add weight, supports needed for spade inset.  Letter embossing doesn't need it.
Spade - Infil to add weight, no supports
Letters - Print flat, already scaled to fit nicely in the embossing
Star - Infil to add weight.

Full print with 4x4x4 walls/top/bottom and 38% infil came to about 48g in weight.  

Glue in lettering and spade.  Star may need minor sanding but should push fit into the space tightly and not need anything else to secure it.

name: Leash Keeper
description:
I take care of my daughter's dog once a week for a couple days while she works.  I needed a way to prevent this crazy 45lb puppy (a boxer) from eating every wood chip, rock, and piece of cat excrement in the yard, while also allowing her to wander in a limited radius, without the leash dragging on the ground and catching on things.  A retractable leash mounted high sounded like the best idea, but I could only commonly find them in 10ft and 16ft maximum extension lengths.  So, I made this device that provides a way to shorten the strap to whatever maximum length I want.

If Thingiverse keeps the photos I uploaded in the proper order, then they show the sequence followed for proper wrapping and securing of the strap on the Leash Keeper.

name: Dogauto3000
description:
Grupo: fideuá con carne (Clara Lado, Irene Martínez y Marcos Viader).

El Dogauto 3000 es un comedero para tu mascota el cual permite al comprador hacer otro tipo de actividades sin preocuparse por la alimentación de su mascota. Este producto alimenta a tu mascota con las cantidades necesarias del pienso de su elección. Al llegar la hora programada (gracias a la tablet que viene incorporada), el Dogauto 3000 dispensa esa cantidad de pienso escogida. Al cabo de un tiempo, se abre una trampilla por donde se tira la comida sobrante. Si se preocupa de la alimentación de su mascota, este producto viene con una cámara a la que se puede conectar por Bluetooth para comprobar su comportamiento y comunicarte con él o ella a través del micrófono incorporado al diseño. Además, el Dogauto 3000 cuenta con un bebedero y dispensador de agua con un sensor para detectar cuando la mascota necesita beber y una gran selección de colores y tamaños para adaptar el producto a su mascota.

name: Turtle basking dock float clip
description:
This is a clip for the struts of large turtle basking docks made by the likes of Zoo Med, Penn Plax and Youthink, to help keep turtles shells dry when they are basking and stop heavy turtles from tipping over the float due to their weight. As basking under a good heat source is an important part of maintaining a turtle's overall health, this is a helpful and useful tool for all turtle caretakers.

In the above example I have a large turtle basking dock so I have printed 4 copies of the clips to support each of the four struts, which helps keep the float in place. The clips are ribbed on the inside so they will not fall off easily. Whilst almost any PLA material can be used, carbon PLA is considered the best for this item. Using your standard 3D printer settings at 30% infill should do the job. It should be noted for best print quality to add a support raft to your print.

name: locking mechanism for a shutter / Einrastmechanismus für eine Tür (Falltür, Schiebetür) - rabbits, chicken, barn, Hühner, Kaninchen, Stall
description:
This was my first project I ever builded myself, and I am still proud of it. It is wear-free and sturdy.
 

This mechanism consist of only two/three printed parts:

A guiding rail (which you might split in half in order to print it)
A spike
You will also need three 3x3x3 mm neodym magnets. One will be inserted into the spike. The second needs to be inserted into the tiny pocket at the left inner side of the upper cylinder. The third is placed in the spike-shaped pocket in which the spike is being locked in. The second and third magnet need to be both fixed in the same polarity position! Fix the spike in inverted magnetic polarity with respect to the other magnets. In the first step, up in the cylinder, it will be attracted and moved into a position from which it will be pushed upwards as soon as you raise the door. When spike gets near its pocket the third magnet will attract the spike so it will automatically snap into its pocket as soon as you let the door down again. Just before, you will hear the spike snap sideways against the guiding rail. In order to release the mechanism again, the door simply has to be pulled up so that the pin in the cylinder points downwards againg due to gravity. Now the door can be lowered again.

Dies war mein erstes Projekt, das ich je selbst entwickelt habe und ich bin immer noch stolz darauf. Es ist verschleißfrei und robust. Dieser Mechanismus besteht aus nur zwei/drei gedruckten Teilen:

Eine Führungsschiene (die ggf. in zwei Hälften geteilt und gedruckt werden muss) 
Einen Dorn
Du benötigst außerdem drei 3x3x3 mm große Neodymmagnete. Einer wird seitlich in den Dorn eingeführt. Der zweite muss in die winzige Tasche an der linken Innenseite des oberen Zylinders eingeführt werden. Der dritte wird in der dornförmige Tasche platziert, in der die Spitze einrasten soll. Der zweite und dritte Magnet müssen beide in gleicher Polaritätslage fixiert werden! Befestige die Spitze in umgekehrter magnetischer Polarität in Bezug auf die anderen Magnete. Im ersten Schritt, oben im Zylinder, wird der Dorn angezogen und in eine Position gebracht, aus der er nach oben gedrückt wird, sobald du die Tür anhebst. Wenn sich der Dorn seiner Tasche nähert, zieht der dritte Magnet den Dorn an, sodass er automatisch in seine Tasche einrastet, sobald du die Tür wieder herunterlässt. Kurz zuvor kann man die Spitze die Führungsschiene schnappen hören. Um den Mechanismus wieder zu lösen, muss die Tür einfach so hoch gezogen werden, dass der Dorn im Zylinder unten  durch die Schwerkraft nach unten zeigt. Nun kann die Tür wieder heruntergelassen werden.

name: Aquarium Water Change - Diaphragm Pump Holder
description:
I use an AutoAqua Smart AWC water change unit on my aquariums. Unfortunately, the pumps that come with the unit are trash. They are flimsy, burn out incredibly easy and the design of the unit means you have to place the pump inside your tank, and inside your water reservoirs. 
I replaced the pumps with 12v Diaphragm pumps purchased off Aliexpress. https://www.aliexpress.com/item/1005002393562141.html?spm=a2g0o.order_list.0.0.24fe1802GrBcfJ
The advantage of these pumps for smaller (Nano and Pico) tanks is they move less water at a time, making them more accurate for small water changes, and they pull water through a hose so the pump itself stays out of the tank. You can easily hook up Auto Top Off and Auto Water Changes with just a hose into the back chamber or corner of your tank.

With the pumps housed outside of the tank, I needed a way to stack them and hold them neatly. I designed a three-chamber box that holds three pumps side by side (for an Auto Water Change that's a tank drain, a tank fill and a freshwater auto top-off pump). The boxes are stackable so however may units you have, you can print multiple boxes. 
Line the cylindrical holder for each pump with some thin adhesive felt to make them extra quiet.

Raw 3mf design files are included if you want to tweak this

name: Abdeckung Strömungspumpe Aquarium (2 Auslässe) Flow Pump Fish Tank
description:
Ich habe diese Abeckungen entworfen, da ich in einem meiner Aquarien Strömungspumpen betreibe, und bei der Strömungspumpe mit den 2 Auslässen leider der Auslass offen ist. Leider sind mir dadurch 2 meiner Tiere in die Pumpenrotoren geschwommen, da kam jede Hilfe zu spät (bin naiver Weise davon ausgegangen, wenn so etwas verkauft wird, das es dann auch sicher ist, leider musste ich die Erfahrung machen das dem nicht so ist).
Ich habe dann verschiedene Varianten dieser Abdeckungen entworfen. Diese wurden von mir in PLA gedruckt und auf die Auslässe gesteckt - jetzt sollte diese Pumpe sicher sein - zumindest für meine Zwecke - kleinere Tiere wie z.B. Neocaridina oder irgendwelche Babyfische & -garnelen dürften da natürlich durch passen, bei solchen Tieren verwendet man aber im Regelfall sowieso keine solchen Pumpen in den Becken.
Enger kann ich die Abdeckungen auch nicht machen, da sonst die Strömung nicht mehr ausreichend gegeben ist.
Vielleicht nützt es ja dem ein oder anderen was, hatte erst versucht auf die schnelle mit Fliegengitter und Gummi drum, damit es zumindest schnell sicher gewesen wäre - allerdings kommt dann eben so gut wie keine Strömung mehr raus, deswegen hab ich diese Teile für mich entworfen und gedruckt und bis jetzt bin ich sehr zufrieden damit, sie tun was sie sollen, sie halten, sie sind so, das meine Tiere nicht mehr in die Pumpe reinschwimmen können - von daher - für mich - perfekt.

ACHTUNG: Ihr müsst die Maße ggf skalieren. Mein erster Versuch war ein bisschen zu groß, hab das Modell dann in Cura durch skalieren auf das richtige Maß gebracht. Was aber bei einer Druckzeit von ca. 15 Min und einem Verbrauch von ca. 2g Filament kein Problem sein sollte ;-)
Hatte in Cura angegeben 43,36mm - Nachgemessen sind es bei mir 42,70mm. Mit dieser Skalierung passt es für mich perfekt, da es nicht zu schwer drauf geht, aber trotz Strömung hält. 

Druckereinstellungen (Anet A8):

Temperatur: 200 Grad (Hotend)

Temperatur Bett: 60 Grad

Druckgeschwindigkeit: 60 mm/sec

Druckplattenhaftung: Skirt

Füllung: 30%

Schichtdicke: 0.16

Have not put them to use yet so the angle might need tweaking.

had to lower the whole print about .2mm into the bed so it wasn't hanging in mid-air.

This is also useful for dog walking at night, with the light on the back of your hand, pointing either forward or backward, you can have some light for visibility as well as keep your hands free for doing dog duty stuff.

Small lizard food dish. This one is 50mm but can be scaled for larger scaled friends. I have printed with supports for the bottom which is concave.

if you enjoy the design, please give it a like. We are working on getting an account set up to allow tipping. Also we have a facebook page, A Baum Creations, so please follow there for more of what we print design!

name: Songmics Klammer für Freigehege
description:
Ich habe mir ein Freigehege für meinen Hamster aus einem Boxregal des Herstellers Songmics gebaut.

name: Aquael Fan mini upgrade large sponge for shrimp safety
description:
This thing is designed to replace the standard Aquael FAN mini filter and possibly other Aquael filter models.

The standard filter is too small for high-quality filtration of water in the aquarium, and the holes in the body are unsafe for shrimp and fish fry, as they are sucked into a trap from which they cannot get out.

To solve the problem, I used a cylindrical sponge 7x14 centimeters.
For a tighter fit on the filter housing, it is necessary to cut off the back decorative wall (alternatively, you can trim the upper part of the sponge to match the shape of the filter)

the set includes sponge tubes with a hole of 10mm and 15mm. There are also covers on the tube in case the sponge has a through hole.

name: Nager: Laufrad
description:
!! Work in progress  !!

Hamster Laufrad

Das Laufrad muss nach dem Druck der vier Viertel zusammengeklebt werden. Innen kann ein Karton oder dünnes Sperrholz rund ausgeschnitten und eingeklebt werden.
Die Achse wird durch 10mm Holzstäbe mit dem Rad verbunden. (Durch die Bohrlöcher können diese verschraubt oder ebenfalls verklebt werden.)

Die Nabe wird ebenfalls mit Stäben mit den unteren beiden Ecken verbunden. In die Nabe kommt ein Lager:
608 ZZ Kugellager, 608zz Metall Double Shielded Miniatur Rillenkugellager (8mm x 22mm x 7mm
https://smile.amazon.de/gp/product/B07VDRZDSC

Die Ecken werden miteinander mittels Stab verbunden.
Nach vorne können zur Stabilisierung weitere Stäbe eingeschoben werden.



Hamster impeller

The wheel must be glued together after printing the four quarters.
The axle is connected to the wheel by 10mm wooden rods. (Through the drilled holes, these can be screwed or glued as well).

The hub is also connected to the bottom two corners with rods.

The corners are connected to each other by means of rods.
Towards the front, more rods can be inserted for stabilization.

name: Quail Rails
description:
Quail rails I've been tinkering around with. It was made for the Little Giant incubator and when assembled it has a capacity of 23 eggs per rail.

Since there is a bit of assembly required I printed mine in ABS. That was simply so I could acetone weld it together. I'm sure any other plastic and superglue would also work.

### Problems ###
These are still a work in progress, comments are most certainly welcome.

1. The cups are too deep and cannot be place next to each other.
1. I would like to redesign the cup so that the bottom collar isn't needed.
1. Tweak the arms that slot into the incubator to remove post processing


### Revisions Made ###
1. Removed the bottom of the cups. Some eggs where hard to get out of the cups, which was annoying when transferring them to lock down. Removing the bottom should make this process easier.
comments: Yeah. They are a little too tall and bump into each other when fully rotated.So meaning they you cannot have 6 of them in the turner, would only be able to do 3?Let me know what you think. I was able to test after posting this and they cannot have other rails near them.Going to give these a shot.  These seem to do well with the larger quail eggs, i am going to see how they rotate as the stock rails for quail are meh.

Modular ant platform. I've made two versions. One with pointed legs, useful for dirt/sand outworlds, as you can dig the legs into the floor and keep it level. Another with flat feet for acrylic/grout bottoms.

name: Kokot: a low energy chicken coop door
description:
Kokot is an Automatic chicken coop door which helps to keep your chickens safe by working on sunrise and sunset hours to open and close.

A chicken coop door is essential and its primary purpose is to provide safety for your chickens from predators.

Kokot is an automatic chicken coop door which works with battery power and solar panel.

It is designed to be as cheap as possible, fully automatic and will be a "low energy" device.

All the design is shared (open hardware and open source) on my hackaday project : 
https://hackaday.io/project/189482-kokot-a-low-energy-chicken-coop-door

The PCB can be ordered at PCBWay although I do have a few spares available: https://www.pcbway.com/project/shareproject/Kokot_a_low_energy_chicken_coop_door_cba5ca2c.html

Everything is printed with free and strong PET filament made from plaxtic bottles : https://hackaday.io/project/185196-pullstruder-from-plastic-bottle-to-pet-filament

description:
The all new large Portaperch can hold more birds for maximum bird capacity. can hold up to 600 birds (depending on size)

A couple minutes in CAD and some time later I have a lid. You can have one if you want.

I sized this for whatever size can Friskies uses. Whatever that size is that's like a tuna can for humans. I don't even know. The lid will probably work for other cans. Bet you could resize it if you wanted. I'm not your boss, but use a twisty motion to break the the vacuum like seal when removing the lid. That's a pro-tip.

name: Chicken waterer (baby chick water)

After just a week they were big enough to drink out of an elevated waterer. So I created this thing so that it can sit on top of a small ceramic bowl. I think it's a fairly standard sized bowl, but you can either scale it or I can upload a different size circle to fit your needs.

If you print the circle with a 5mm brim, you don't even have to remove the brim and it will actually assist you in the gluing process for more surface area. I highly recommend using epoxy as super glue doesn't work very well with 3D prints.

I also recommend 3 walls for water proofing purposes. But it can be printed at 10% infill with 6 top layers.

name: Formicarium - Tube Expansion
description:
# Formicarium - Tube Expansion

This is a set of useful parts that I use when the size of the current formicarium is not sufficient anymore.

It is designed for 160mm x 16mm test tubes and tubing with 14mm outer diameter.

**Entrance**

The entrance part has open holes for the ants to enter or exit the expansion.
7 test tubes can be inserted for the ants to enter.

**Support**

This part is used to support the back of the test tubes so that they all stay aligned and level with the entrance.

**Spacer**

The spacer can be used to fixate the distance between entrance and support so that the 160mm test tubes do not become loose all of a sudden.

**Connectors**

A collection of tubing connectors compatible with 14mm outer diameter tubing and the entrance part.

**Terminators**

Two different terminators can be attached to tubing so that the way is closed. 

- a closed terminator
- a 2 part air terminator where you can put a mesh so that air flow is possible.

name: Cat Corner Rub - 2hr 30g Vase Mode
description:
I saw someone else post one and it reminded me I always wanted to make one ultra light versatile and vase mode!

You print this with 0.4mm and 0.2mm layer height. with a 0.6mm nozzle if you scale it up slightly say 25% it should slice without busting vase mode (the ribs are dimensionally important in slicing)

less than 2 hours to print less than 30g of plastic in vase mode no top no bottom layers.

You can double stick tape to the wall or use the flat plates on the sides screw right through them into the wall.

name: LED strip mount for Fluval Flex 37
description:
The LED strip in my Fluval Flex 37 burned out, and I wanted a bit more light than the stock config - there are two versions of the holder, one for standard LED strip and one for IP67 silicone sleeved LEDs. 

I ordered 144 LED/m 2812/5050 RGB LEDs to give it some extra light - you should be able to fit between 55 and 100 LEDs (if you also use the stock tube), vs 36 for the stock config.

If you use the standard, unsleeved version, use the 12mm channel and you'll need to waterproof either with an acrylic cover or using epoxy to seal them in (not sure about the heat from the LEDs though.

For the silicone-sleeved LEDs, print two end caps and slot them under the holder on each end. You could print a third one for the middle for extra support, but I don't think it's necessary.

I'm driving with an arduino nano (using the NEOPIXEL library for 2812 LEDs) that receives input from a Raspberry Pi with 16x2 LCD shield to change scenes and schedule the lights.

name: Cat Tree Pillar Mount, internal nut
description:
This mount matches the internal diameter of my particular cat tree pillar, 60mm, to replace the broken mount. It stuffs inside the pillar and a bolt interfaces with the embedded hex nut. The friction fit of the mount seems good enough but you could add glue, maybe, or perhaps staples from the outside to more permanently embed this mount.

This print must be paused mid way through to place the hex nut (M8 maybe? It's 7mm tall and 14mm between flats) into the space, before the top of that chamber is printed. Use your slicer to do this, otherwise you just have to manually pause the print when it looks like it's almost done with that part.

Also note that there is a very slight taper to the outer walls of this model, so the top is slightly thinner than the bottom, such that it can be inserted easier beginning with the top.

name: Fishmate Stack

This is an extension to mount a second Fishmate aquarium feeder on top of the first feeder.

In a stacked configuration, one Fishmate feeds in the AM while the second Fishmate feeds in the PM, enabling twice-a-day feedings for 14 days before refill.

name: (Pet Enrichment Toy) Turntable Starfish
description: This is a pet enrichment toy, it is intended to make the act of foraging more stimulating for your animal. Simply put a treat or morsel under each of the sliders then give the toy to your pet and leave it to them to work out how to retrieve the treats. The design is based on something I saw for a small dog, although I've recreated it for my pet rats. I imagine it would be equally suitable for other rodents and perhaps parrots. I would like to be able to say my rats have shown a real aptitude for problem-solving... however, the sad truth is most of their success with this toy has been down to perseverance and dumb luck! That notwithstanding, it's been entertaining to watch all the same :) Enjoy! For more of my pet enrichment toys and accessories check out Rat Toys & Cage Accessories Update: I have added two additional Spinners. name: Chux Wall Clip
description:
It's a sad reality that as our pets get older they suffer the same ravages of age as we do. My oldest dog is suffering greatly from arthritis in her knees and hips. She has trouble walking, and frequently falls on our hardwood floors. (We've put rugs and carpet down everywhere we can.) Another unfortunate side effect is that she has a lot of trouble squatting, so she can't potty outside much any more. She tries to hold it, but has frequent accidents while she sleeps.

With that in mind, I designed this clip to attach [Chux Pads](https://amzn.com/B000RDRRVK) to the wall via [Command Strips](https://amzn.com/B000FDLFBK). They make cleanup easier, and prevent any getting smushed in the baseboard heaters.

name: Top Load Hopper v3
description:
So the other version I made was a flop, because the girls immediately decided its best use would be to empty it entirely and hide inside it. I'm glad they enjoyed it but I needed an efficient way to feed them, they had plenty of hidey holes already. 

Enter this version. So far, so good. They still dig some of the food out to get at the peanuts (I add peanuts to their blocks because the blocks really don't have enough fat in them) but most of it seems to be intact and they aren't nibbling the plastic yet. If they do decide to gnaw the "basket" at the bottom open, I'll cave in and attach wire, but for now I'll see if this works for them because I'd rather they mash their faces against soft plastic than hard and potentially poky wire mesh.

This thing was made with Tinkercad. Edit it online https://www.tinkercad.com/things/0q92xd9m8mv

name: Nicrew Automatic Feeder Reduction Rings
description:
I recently purchased a Nicrew Automatic Feeder due to it's non-rotating drum design. I modded my RedSea Max 130C reef tank to have a cutout at the rear of the hood so that I could mount an automatic feeder. However, the problem with most auto-feeders is that they have a rotating feed drum which had a tendency to get hung up on the hood unless they were positioned perfectly. The Nicrew instead uses an internal hopper to deliver the food. However in it's stock configuration, it delivers way too much if using small pellets and there's no built-in way to reduce that. (a major design flaw IMHO)... 

So Tinkercad and  Ender 3 to the rescue!... By removing the three screws that holds the endcap on, the spring loaded door (plunger) can be removed and one of these reduction rings slid in to reduce the size of the feed opening. I made three thickness 3mm, 3.5mm, and 4mm. The thicker (larger) the ring, the less food is dropped.

Note: If you print all three you can store the two unused sizes under/inside the encap for later use (e.g your number/size of fish or food size/type changes)

name: München Hundesteuermark Geräuschreduzierer // Munich Dog Tax Tag Noise Reducer
description:
Background: in Germany, dogs must wear a special tag from the local government signifying that dog tax has been paid. This is in addition to the customary name tag with contact information in case the dog is found. Two metal tags on a single collar is a recipe for mind-jarring noise, so I designed this bumper for my Munich dog tax tag to reduce the noise.

I'm happy to report that this bumper works beyond my original expectations. I printed in FormFutura CarbonFiln at 240 degrees C, but a test print in FormFutura PLA/HPA at 205 degrees worked even better. There is a slight overhang (required for the tag to fit around the tax tag) and so this print is rather sensitive to settings. I printed without supports -- I didn't try it with!

name: CO2 diffuser booster
description:
This improves efficiency of the EHEIM CO2-SET Diffuser 400l by connecting it to an external filter outlet. (https://eheim.com/en_GB/complement/accessories/co2-diffusor-400). 

The original diffuser works, but some of the bubbles are quite large and won't get dissolved.

This thing is connected to the outlet of an external filter or other pump. The water flows over the diffuser stone at relatively high speed and drags the CO2 along in the shape of very small, mostly invisible, bubbles.

Fits the 30 mm round diffuser and 12 mm (i.d.) hose. Use for instance zip tie, rubber band or fishing line to tie it all together.

*WARNING!* The booster could possibly increase the risk of water getting siphoned backways if the CO2 line looses pressure (e.g. during bottle change) - take precautions: 
- Disconnect the diffuser when doing maintenance on the CO2 side
- Use double check valves on the CO2 line
- Perhaps keep the fish tank in the bathroom!

name: Portion Reducer for Automatic Fish Feeder
description:
This little insert reduces the portions of the very common mini automatic fish feeder you find on sites like aliexpress. Even with the minimum settings of 1 portion every 3 days, the feeder would overfeed my nano tanks. The reducer comes in three sizes, a comparison between the stock feeder and the reducer (small version) can be seen in the pictures. I used Ocean Nutrition "Community Formula Pellets" for the testing.

It is very easy to install, just requiring you to unscrew the four screws under the feeder and pushing it into the slot on the feeder mechanism.

Align the hole with the rubber pad in the feeder, putting it the other way might jam your feeder.

Note: The insert is deliberately oversized so that you have to force it in. If it fits loosely it might come off and get lost within the feeder or might otherwise jam it.

name: Aquarium Filter Return Flow Control (Tetra)
description:
If you have aquarium inhabitants (such as Axolotls) that don't like fast-moving surface water, such as those created by a waterfall effect from a filter return. I created a water flow diverter that you can hang on the side of your tank where your filter return is. Using this diverter, the water will be moved to the back glass of your tank instead of creating the waterfall effect.

I also included an optional top cover if you want to not see the water return.

This model was designed for a Tetra Whisper 20 Filter on a Tetra 20-gallon aquarium, so it may need to be adjusted for your needs.

name: Aquarium Filter Return Flow Control (Aqueon QuietFlow Canister Filter)
description:
If you have aquarium inhabitants (such as Axolotls) that don't like fast-moving surface water, such as those created by a waterfall effect from a filter return. I created a water flow diverter that you can hang on the side of your tank where your filter return is. Using this diverter, the water will be moved to the back glass of your tank instead of creating the waterfall effect.

This model comes in 3 parts, a left side, a right side, and arms. The arms can be slid in/out to fit the lip of your aquarium. The left and right sides should clip in place, but you can optionally use glue placed in the upper connector hole to affix them together (I don't, but it's up to you).

This model was designed for an Aqueon QuietFlow Canister Filter return on a 44-gallon aquarium, so it may need to be adjusted for your needs.

# Platform for Dog Toys

This is the base unit of a platform that you (and everyone) can build upon.  The idea behind this is that you print this base one time and then you can create and print things (games) that go __on top__ of this base.  If the top needs to be attached to the base, then you can use the holes to align it and then use bolts to attach it to the base.

name: 20G Sump Filter Sock Holder
description:
I created this design to replace a broken insert kit for 20gallon long aquarium converted to a sump.  Rather than purchase a new insert kit, I decided to design this to correct things I didn't like about the old kit.

Improvements over old insert design:
1.) The socks are raised out of the tank a little father allowing for them to be more easily replaced.  I also think that this position makes them more efficient too, but I can't say for sure.
2.) The socks share a basin so that when the primary sock gets clogged, the overflow goes to the secondary sock before entering the sump.
3.) There is a spillway as an overflow in case both socks get clogged.  Although that shouldn't be possible if you're changing the socks as often as you should.

I printed an earlier revision with an extended spillway that didn't print as well as I wanted, so I made some improvements on this revision.  I'm open to any and all suggestions for improvements.

PS: I used this with a reef diaper filter sock because I hate cleaning filter socks, and because the adapter has a nice rubberized ring amount the outside that creates a tight seal between the sock and sock holder so water can't escape around it.  This should still work with a regular sock, but overflow from a clogged sock may go through the small crack around it rather than flowing to the other sock as intended.

name: Fish Feeding Enclosures Fluval Flex 15

The suction cup holders are a universal wedge shaped design. I used a medium sized or 30mm diameter purchased from any craft store.

You may need to train your fish to enter the enclosure for feeding. I used my finger on the glass to guide my Betta. The The Fluval Flex Feeding Door by FishGuildCorp on Etsy has been my feeding door since the start, and it has a nice thud when closing to signal the fish to a feeding time further. 

I 3d model as a hobby; if able, tip any charity you choose.

name: Hood for "Interpet Kids Glow White and Blue LED Light for Aquarium"
description:
This is a hood specifically designed to fit over an "Interpet Kids Glow White and Blue LED Light for Aquarium", as per from Amazon (https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B06W9FWLN8).

It's a cheap basic little light that works okay as a nightlight, but when mounted on the glass inside a rimless aquarium with a glass lid you can see the LEDs directly, and they're quite blinding, distracting, and unpleasant to look at. This print shades the light so the LEDs aren't directly visible.

I've printed it in black so it's less obvious in the aquarium and less likely to grow algae, and I've lined the inside with the aluminium kitchen foil - not sure how much this really helps! You'll need superglue for the tin foil. After placing the tin foil give it a rinse and look out for small flakes of foil going into the water.

The hood fits quite loosely so it's easy to remove.

If your aquarium already has a full hood then you probably don't need this print.

It prints easily in about 3-4 hours. Place it upside down on the build-plate - the model is already orientated appropriately.

name: Universal Happy Poo Bag Holder
description:
This is a version 3. The only difference is it is printed as one piece. 
This an update and rework of my Happy Poo Bag holder (3D design Happy poo bag clip for flat leash ver 2.1 | Tinkercad).

Nothing is more inconvenient than holding a poo bag and walking the dog. Especially if you walk two dogs or your dog does multiple jobs in one walk.

This model will work on a flat leash of most standard widths and on the typical round or rope style leash. Also beefed up the side holders and added round ends to avoid possible snapping and catching on clothing. Added slots for zip ties on round leash.

(If used on a flat style leash you print two clips and glue on to the back side of the bag holder with the open slots facing out. for version 2.1 only) Then slip the leash into the slots, being sure to face the hooks up towards the leash handle (see arrow on flip side of holder).

(If used on a round or rope style leash do not print the clips version 2.1 only), but instead use zip ties to lash the holder to the rope, being sure have it face up as the arrow indicated on one side of holder.

(Note #1: You can glue the flat leash clips and still use the round rope with the zip ties.)

Note #2: I suggest you couple my Happy Face Poo Bag Holder with my remixed version (https://www.tinkercad.com/things/ceMTHnkI3W9-dog-poo-bag-holder-modified) of Dog Poop Bag Holder by teamxeri - Thingiverse and you have a complete system.

name: TkStar TK906 Dog Collar Clip / Holder
description:
The TkStar TK906 GPS tracker is developed for use as a led light and tracker for your bike but i wanted to use it as a cheap tracker for my dog, so i made this custom holder / clip that slides on the dog collar band and makes it easy to clip on and off the tracker when you need to.

***To use this clip you need to remove (saw off) the mount holders on the backside of the tracker so the backside is a flat surface***

The tracker only fits one way since the top and bottom radius is different.

This clip fits collars that are 20mm in width and 2mm thickness. I've added the FreeCad project file so you can edit the model if you need to.

name: Verschluss Katzenfutter BOZITA Tetra Pak
description:
Habe mir hier einen Verschluss für das Katzenfutter von BOZITA im Tetra Pak gebastelt, damit das Futter nicht offen rumsteht und vertrocknet, da wir nicht eine volle Packung am Tag füttern.

I made a closure for the BOZITA cat food in the Tetra Pak so that the food doesn't stand around open and dry out, since we don't feed a full pack a day.

name: Repile WormProof Dish
description:
This is a re-post of a print from my alternate maker account (Coolcat832001). This worm dish is perfect for many insectivores. The rounded design ensures superworms, mealworms, and waxworms stay in the bowl. This was drawn for myself to aid a handicapped gecko. 

Best printed using a raft or brim. Does not require supports. 
70% scale is ideal for most leopard geckos, 100% scale is recommended for Bearded Dragons or other large lizards.

name: Protein Skimmer for Saltwater
description:
Made this for my nano reef tank. 3 Parts so it can easily be printed on smaller printers as well. The bottom part has a hole that fits a standard air hose, pull that one trough and then attach an air diffusor on the other side.

The holder are tank specific for my fish tank and might need modification. But the Skimmer has also 3 loops along the side, so you can come up with something completely different, e.g. using a string and a counter weight.

The height should be adjusted so that the skimmer cup barely touches the water surface. Regulate the airflow so it doesn't create too many bubbles .You want the skimmed solution to be dark brown to black. Not some yellow or clear stuff that means its running too wet.

I recommend only using PETG as its safest for the water if used for a fish tank.

I added an alternative version for the middle part (SkimmerB2) that has a longer return pipe to create less micro bubbles. In general, the more airflow the more micro bubbles but also the better skimming. I might make a version in future that gets completely rid of them. But as of now I don't mind the optics in my tank and if you have a separate sump its not an issue at all.

description: 8mm narrower

name: Rollermat Reef Filter Body Hexagons
description:
Different version of the body for https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5283760

Attempting to avoid support material.

Attached are the fusion 360 files this was created in. I made it by importing the original's STL into fusion 360, doing a bit of measuring and sizing guessing, and then recreating from scratch with those dimensions.

The generation of the hexagons and management of them could be cleaner, but this works.

Currently attempting to print it with supports angle at 70° which avoids it building support in the hexagons and 0.3 layer height (nozzle = 0.6). TBD if it prints cleanly.

name: Choubox Litter Guard
description:
This is a guard for the Choubox automatic litter box. It stops the cats kicking out the litter onto the floor.
It's a friction fit so easy install.

made of PLA

name: Bluebird House Entrance Guard With and Without Extension and Perch
description:
This is a print that I made for a bird house critter guard. 

The opening is 1.5" and there are two prints. One that incorporates a small perch for the bird to land on and has a hole extension and the second is a guard only. Both the bottom of the bird hole and the perch have small cutouts that help the bird with traction and grabbing.

I have printed this with 40% infill and 100% infill and both came out great.

Does require support for the small perch.

name: Low poly laying golden retreaver
description: So I recently made a model to remember my most recently deceased dog, and I realized I wanted one for each of my pets that have passed on. So here is another one. I didn't add wings to this one as I actually found out, I actually didn't like it. As the dog I based this on had passed away more then a decade ago, I had trouble finding reference photos for this. In the end, I found a silhouette online that looked similar and then modeled it, rigged it, and posed it. Then used that as a reference to make a low poly. It was a long process but I think it turned out pretty good. Plus I think that it is low poly enough that it can be for any golden. I hope you enjoy.

name: Golden Retriever laying with optional wings
description: I recently lost my dog, so I wanted to print something out to remind me of him. Most of the golden retrievers models I found online didn't feel close enough, so I made my own. The basic model is called "without wings" and features a golden retriever laying down with all legs spread. I separated the winged model into two parts, the wings and the dog. You can glue them together if you want to but they should just slide in.

name: Aqueon Fish Tank Lid: Size 2.5
description:
After seeing that the fish tank lids cost more than the tank itself, I decided I would make my own AND give it cute windows.

I intended for the windows to give some airflow which I think is good for the betta fish, but I'm not a fish expert. 

I printed this in two parts and upside down to minimize supports. If made, be careful not to stress the windows when removing the supports, as they are easily damaged.

name: Pet sign
description:
I made this sign so my wife and I will know if there other one has already fed our dog.

Similar to the "clean/ dirty" dishwasher signs. If you just gave your dog breakfast you slide the slide to cover the word "breakfast" so it will read "I want dinner" and vice versa. Fairly self explanatory. Probably would work for kids also if you don't give them lunch and don't feel like just asking them.

Just place the slide on the "breakfast dinner" section and then glue the "I Want" section on top.

My wife painted it beforehand so it didn't look to boring but I'm not going to tell you how to live your life.

name: Juwel Aquarium 89000 EasyFeed Upgrade
description:
For everyone who´s struggling with the Juwel Aquarium Automatic Feeder due to clumping up here´s a solution which works even if the Food gets clumped up. 

Everything fits tightly (except the Funnel). Install the Spiral first and then the Case.

name: Ugly Latch
description:
I originally printed savingprivatebrian15's latch but found that the pin was too small for the latch boor of my doors, and under its own weight it would just pop off. After trying to widen the pin at the end of the printed latch, it held better, but my dog could still get through.

This very ugly latch is my first time even touching Blender to widen the pin, lengthen the pin height, and add an overhang that locks it into the hardware on my door frame.
comments: Definitely not my best work, I was pretty hasty with my design and later made some small changes that I never got around to uploading. Appreciate you taking the time to improve upon it though, hope you find it useful!

name: Aquarium Rim Planter
description:
Aquarium / Paludarium corner plant pot.

ONLY PRINT IN FOOD SAFE PLASTICS such as PETG. 

DO NOT PRINT IN PLA - THIS IS TOXIC TO AQUATIC CREATURES

-If you want to add natural filtration to your aquarium.
-2" and 3" deep pots.
-Fill pots with gravel, coarse sand, or other ceramic medium.
-Designed for standard tanks with rim.

name: fish tank plant topper
description:
A toper made to go on a standard fish tank, allows a tray/bed area for water to run(approximately an inch of water) a filter and plants can be put here to help clean the fish water and grow simple plants in. the flowing water should also oxygenate the water enough to not need an air stone(all at your own risk)
4 of the holes are 27mm and a 3/4 “ pipe should fit inside of it to build up if you desire, the other holes you can design around and use to hold toppers over the bed area or whatever people come up with.

you do not need every pin inserted they are more to guide it for the lock pieces(may need to adjust the lock piece sizes tight tolerances, of the uploads one set is exported from bambu slicer exactly as I printed it.

name: Dog leash holder
description:
I designed this to hold my leash, I wanted something small, that doesn't take long to print.
On the backside, I used double sided tape to hold it on the wall.
I used 100% infill so it would be strong, but you can try it with less infill.

name: Wombaroo Marsupial Teat Bottle Adapter (Kanagaroo/Wombat)
description:
When raising joey's they quickly out grow the standard wombaroo feed bottles, due to the womabaroo teats having a very narrow neck larger bottles are hard to find to suit the teats.

This adapter allows you to use a standard soft drink bottle (glass or plastic)
